   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>Hey int3, thanks for the code!

It looks like a bit more work will be needed to get this into shippable shape.
Two tasks in particular:

== 1. JSON serialization of tags ==

When I run the code with your patch included, and I load the widget for someone
who has the tag "I will never understand Deleuze", I get this traceback:

Traceback:
File "/home/raffi/oh/milestone-a/parts/mysite/django/core/handlers/base.py" in
get_response
  99.                     response = callback(request, *callback_args,
**callback_kwargs)
File "/home/raffi/oh/milestone-a/mysite/profile/views.py" in widget_display_json
  174.     json = simplejson.dumps(data, cls=django_json_encoder)
File
"/home/raffi/oh/milestone-a/eggs/simplejson-2.1.1-py2.6-linux-i686.egg/simplejson/__init__.py"
in dumps
  268.         use_decimal=use_decimal, **kw).encode(obj)
File
"/home/raffi/oh/milestone-a/eggs/simplejson-2.1.1-py2.6-linux-i686.egg/simplejson/encoder.py"
in encode
  214.         chunks = self.iterencode(o, _one_shot=True)
File
"/home/raffi/oh/milestone-a/eggs/simplejson-2.1.1-py2.6-linux-i686.egg/simplejson/encoder.py"
in iterencode
  282.             return _iterencode(o, 0)
File "/home/raffi/oh/milestone-a/mysite/profile/views.py" in default
  170.             return simplejson.JSONEncoder.default(self, obj)
File
"/home/raffi/oh/milestone-a/eggs/simplejson-2.1.1-py2.6-linux-i686.egg/simplejson/encoder.py"
in default
  190.         raise TypeError(repr(o) + " is not JSON serializable")

Exception Type: TypeError at /people/rafpaf/openhatch-widget.json
Exception Value: &lt;Tag: understands_not: Deleuze&gt; is not JSON serializable

== 2. User privacy ==

Another task for you is to keep some of our users' data private. For instance,
tags are public, but fields like these should be kept out of the JSON:
location_confirmed, blacklisted_repository_committers, show_email,
expand_next_steps, dont_guess_my_location. That's an incomplete list. I suppose
the best solution is to JSON-ify only the fields you're interested in (projects,
tags, etc.)

Thanks again for your contributions so far, int3!

(By the way, Deleuze is &lt;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gilles_Deleuze">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gilles_Deleuze</a>&gt;, a
difficult philosopher.)</pre>
   </td>
